Science&rdquo;, <em>Law Library Journal</em>, 76(1):
78&ndash;120.</li>

<li>White, Howard B., 1968, <em>Peace among the Willows: The Political
Philosophy of Francis Bacon</em> (International Archives of the
History of Ideas 24), The Hague: Martinus Nijhoff.</li>

<li>Zagorin, Perez, 1998, <em>Francis Bacon</em>, Princeton, NJ:
Princeton University Press.</li>

</ul>

<h3 id="OthImpWor">Other Important Works</h3>

<ul class="hanging">

<li>Agassi, Joseph, 2013, <em>The Very Idea of Modern Science: Francis
Bacon and Robert Boyle</em> (Boston Studies in the Philosophy and
History of Science, 298), Dordrecht/New York: Springer.
doi:10.1007/978-94-007-5351-8</li>

<li>Belkind, Ori, 2021, &ldquo;Bacon&rsquo;s Inductive Method and
Material Form&rdquo;, <em>Epistemology &amp; Philosophy of
Science</em>, 58(3): 57&ndash;68. doi:10.5840/eps202158343</li>

<li>&Ccedil;akan, Melike, forthcoming, &ldquo;Common Good in Francis
Bacon&rsquo;s (1561&ndash;1626) &lsquo;Human Philosophy&rsquo;&rdquo;,
in <em>In Search of the Common Good</em>, Adriana Luna-Fabritius
(ed.), Leiden/Boston: Brill.</li>

<li>Cassan, &Eacute;lodie, 2021, &ldquo;Bacon&rsquo;s <em>Novum
Organum</em>: &lsquo;The Marriage Bed Between the Mind and the
Universe&rsquo;&rdquo;, <em>Epistemology &amp; Philosophy of
Science</em>, 58(3): 38&ndash;46. doi:10.5840/eps202158341</li>

<li>Corneanu, Sorana, 2015, &ldquo;Francis Bacon on Charity and the
Ends of Knowledge&rdquo;, in <em>Conflicting Values of Inquiry:
Ideologies of Epistemology in Early Modern Europe</em>, Tam&aacute;s
Demeter, Kathryn Murphy, and Klaus Zittel (eds), Leiden: Brill,
339&ndash;364.</li>

<li>Drozdova, Daria N., 2021, &ldquo;Francis Bacon, Between Myth and
History&rdquo;, <em>Epistemology &amp; Philosophy of Science</em>,
58(3): 6&ndash;21. doi:10.5840/eps202158339</li>

<li>Dumitru, Claudia, 2020, &ldquo;Francis Bacon and the Aristotelian
Tradition on the Nature of Sound&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#JV2020">Jalobeanu and Vida 2020</a>:
 9&ndash;25. doi:10.5840/jems20209211</li>

<li>Elliot, Natalie, 2015, &ldquo;The Politics of Life Extension in
Francis Bacon&rsquo;s <em>Wisdom of the Ancients</em>&rdquo;, <em>The
Review of Politics</em>, 77(3): 351&ndash;375.
doi:10.1017/S0034670515000327</li>

<li>Farrington, Benjamin, 1964, <em>The Philosophy of Francis Bacon:
An Essay on Its Development from 1603 to 1609 with New Translation of
Fundamental Texts</em>, Liverpool: Liverpool University Press.</li>

<li>Fattori, Marta (ed.), 1984, <em>Francis Bacon: Terminologia e
fortuna nel XVII secolo</em>, Roma: Edizioni dell&rsquo;Ateneo.</li>

<li>Fitzmaurice, Andrew, 2007, &ldquo;The Commercial Ideology of
Colonization in Jacobean England: Robert Johnson, Giovanni Botero, and
the Pursuit of Greatness&rdquo;, <em>The William and Mary
Quarterly</em>, 64(4): 791&ndash;820. doi:10.2307/25096750</li>

<li>Fuller, Steve, 2021, &ldquo;The Prophetic Bacon: Response to
Garber&rdquo;, <em>Epistemology &amp; Philosophy of Science</em>,
58(3): 78&ndash;86. doi:10.5840/eps202158345</li>

<li>Garber, Daniel, 2020, &ldquo;Margaret Cavendish among the
Baconians&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#JV2020">Jalobeanu and Vida 2020</a>:
 53&ndash;84. doi:10.5840/jems20209213</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2021, &ldquo;Bacon&rsquo;s Metaphysical
Method&rdquo;, <em>Epistemology &amp; Philosophy of Science</em>,
58(3): 22&ndash;37. doi:10.5840/eps202158340</li>

<li>Gaskell, Philip, 1979, &ldquo;Books Bought by Whitgift&rsquo;s
Pupils in the 1570s&rdquo;, <em>Transactions of the Cambridge
Bibliographical Society</em>, 7(3): 284&ndash;293.</li>

<li>Gemelli, Benedino, 2012, &ldquo;The History of Life and Death A
&lsquo;Spiritual&rsquo; History from Invisible Matter to Prolongation
of Life&rdquo;, <em>Early Science and Medicine</em>, 17(1&ndash;2):
134&ndash;157. doi:10.1163/157338212X631819</li>

<li>Guillory, John, 2009, &ldquo;The Bachelor State: Philosophy and
Sovereignty in Bacon&rsquo;s <em>New Atlantis</em>&rdquo;, in
<em>Politics and the Passions, 1500-1850</em>, Victoria Kahn, Neil
Saccamano, and Daniela Coli (eds), Princeton, NJ: Princeton University
Press, 49&ndash;74.</li>

<li>Hale, Kimberly Hurd, 2013, <em>Francis Bacon&rsquo;s New Atlantis
in the Foundation of Modern Political Thought</em>, Lanham, MD:
Lexington Books.</li>

<li>Hartmann, Anna&#8208;Maria, 2015, &ldquo;The Strange Antiquity of
Francis Bacon&rsquo;s <em>New Atlantis</em>&rdquo;, <em>Renaissance
Studies</em>, 29(3): 375&ndash;393. doi:10.1111/rest.12084</li>

<li>Iorizzo, Dolores, 2021, &ldquo;Self-Preservation and the
Transformation of Nature: A Response to Garber&rdquo;,
<em>Epistemology &amp; Philosophy of Science</em>, 58(3): 47&ndash;56.
doi:10.5840/eps202158342</li>

<li>Jalobeanu, Dana, 2012b, &ldquo;Idolatry, Natural History,
and Spiritual Medicine: Francis Bacon and the Neo-Stoic Protestantism
of the Late Sixteenth Century&rdquo;, <em>Perspectives on
Science</em>, 20(2): 207&ndash;226. doi:10.1162/POSC_a_00063</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2015, <em>The Art of Experimental Natural
History: Francis Bacon in Context</em>, Bucharest: Zeta Books.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2018b, &ldquo;Rewriting Bacon&rsquo;s
Natural History: Pierre Amboise&rsquo;s Translation of <em>Sylva
Sylvarum</em>&rdquo;, in <em>Natural History in Early Modern France:
The Poetics of an Epistemic Genre</em> (Intersections 58),
Rapha&euml;l Garrod and Paul J. Smith (eds), Leiden: Brill,
180&ndash;204. doi:10.1163/9789004375703_010</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2021a, &ldquo;Francis Bacon&rsquo;s
&lsquo;Perceptive&rsquo; Instruments&rdquo;, <em>Early Science and
Medicine</em>, 25(6): 594&ndash;617.
doi:10.1163/15733823-00256P04</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2021b, &ldquo;On Metaphysics and Method, Or
How to Read Francis Bacon&rsquo;s <em>Novum Organum</em>&rdquo;,
<em>Epistemology &amp; Philosophy of Science</em>, 58(3):
98&ndash;118. doi:10.5840/eps202158347</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2022, &ldquo;Dissecting Nature <em>ad
vivum</em>: Parts and Wholes in Francis Bacon&rsquo;s Natural
Philosophy&rdquo;, <em>Bruniana &amp; Campanelliana</em>, 28:
165&ndash;182.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, forthcoming, &ldquo;Creating Life in the
Laboratory: Francis Bacon&rsquo;s Journey from Living Spirits to
Animate Bodies&rdquo;, <em>Notes and Records: The Royal Society
Journal of the History of Science</em>, first online: 10 January 2024,
rsnr.2023.0037. doi:10.1098/rsnr.2023.0037</li>

<li>Jardine, Lisa, 1974, <em>Francis Bacon: Discovery and the Art of
Discourse</em>, London/New York: Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Jardine, Lisa and Alan Stewart, 1998, <em>Hostage to Fortune: The
Troubled Life of Francis Bacon</em>, London: Victor Gollancz.</li>

<li>Kocher, Paul H., 1957, &ldquo;Francis Bacon on the Science of
Jurisprudence&rdquo;, <em>Journal of the History of Ideas</em>, 18(1):
3&ndash;26. doi:10.2307/2707577</li>

<li>Langman, A. P., 2010, &ldquo;The Future Now: Chance, Time and
Natural Divination in the Thought of Francis Bacon&rdquo;, in <em>The
Uses of the Future in Early Modern Europe</em>, Andreas Brady and
Emily Butterworth (eds), New York: Routledge, 142&ndash;158.</li>

<li>Lynch, William, 2021, &ldquo;Method and Control: Naturalizing
Scientific Culture in Bacon&rsquo;s Novum Organum&rdquo;,
<em>Epistemology &amp; Philosophy of Science</em>, 58(3): 69&ndash;77.
doi:10.5840/eps202158344</li>

<li>Manzo, Silvia, 2012, &ldquo;Francis Bacon&rsquo;s Natural History
and Civil History: A Comparative Survey&rdquo;, <em>Early Science and
Medicine</em>, 17(1&ndash;2): 32&ndash;61.
doi:10.1163/157338212X631774</li>

<li>McCutcheon, Elizabeth, 1972, &ldquo;Bacon and the Cherubim: An
Iconographical Reading of the <em>New Atlantis</em>&rdquo;,
<em>English Literary Renaissance</em>, 2(3): 334&ndash;355.
doi:10.1111/j.1475-6757.1972.tb01000.x</li>

<li>Milner, Benjamin, 1997, &ldquo;Francis Bacon: The Theological
Foundations of <em>Valerius Terminus</em>&rdquo;, <em>Journal of the
History of Ideas</em>, 58(2): 245&ndash;264.
doi:10.1353/jhi.1997.0020</li>

<li>Minkov, Svetozar, 2009, &ldquo;Baconian Science and the
Intelligibility of Human Experience: The Case of Love&rdquo;, <em>The
Review of Politics</em>, 71(3): 389&ndash;410.
doi:10.1017/S0034670509990027</li>

<li>Omodeo, Pietro Daniel, 2021, &ldquo;Bacon&rsquo;s Anthropocene:
The Historical-Epistemological Entanglement of Power, Knowledge and
Nature Reassessed&rdquo;, <em>Epistemology &amp; Philosophy of
Science</em>, 58(3): 149&ndash;170. doi:10.5840/eps202158350</li>

<li>Osminskaya, Natalia A., 2021, &ldquo;Language of Reality and
Reality of Language in Francis Bacon&rsquo;s Philosophy&rdquo;,
<em>Epistemology &amp; Philosophy of Science</em>, 58(3):
119&ndash;131. doi:10.5840/eps202158348</li>

<li>Patterson, Timothy H., 1989, &ldquo;The Secular Control of
Scientific Power in the Political Philosophy of Francis Bacon&rdquo;,
<em>Polity</em>, 21(3): 457&ndash;480. doi:10.2307/3234743</li>

<li>Peltonen, Markku, 1992, &ldquo;Politics and Science: Francis Bacon
and the True Greatness of States&rdquo;, <em>The Historical
Journal</em>, 35(2): 279&ndash;305. doi:10.1017/S0018246X00025802</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2001a, &ldquo;Francis Bacon, the Earl of
Northampton, and the Jacobean Anti-Duelling Campaign&rdquo;, <em>The
Historical Journal</em>, 44(1): 1&ndash;28.
doi:10.1017/S0018246X01001649</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2001b, &ldquo;&lsquo;The Miller of
Hungtingdon&rsquo;: Francis Bacon - Statesman and Philosopher&rdquo;,
<em>Redescriptions: Political Thought, Conceptual History and Feminist
Theory</em>, 5(1): 34&ndash;52. doi:10.7227/R.5.1.3</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2004 [2007], &ldquo;Bacon, Francis,
Viscount St Alban (1561&ndash;1626), Lord Chancellor, Politician, and
Philosopher&rdquo;, in <em>The Oxford Dictionary of National
Biography</em>, H. C. G. Matthew and B. Harrison (eds), Oxford: Oxford
University Press, ref:odnb/990. This version 4 October 2007; accessed
24 January 2025. doi:10.1093/ref:odnb/990</li>

<li>P&eacute;rez-Ramos, Antonio, 1988, <em>Francis Bacon&rsquo;s Idea
of Science and the Maker&rsquo;s Knowledge Tradition</em>, Oxford/New
York: Clarendon Press.</li>

<li>Pesic, Peter, 2014, &ldquo;Francis Bacon, Violence, and the Motion
of Liberty: The Aristotelian Background&rdquo;, <em>Journal of the
History of Ideas</em>, 75(1): 69&ndash;90.
doi:10.1353/jhi.2014.0007</li>

<li>Price, Bronwen (ed.), 2002, <em>Francis Bacon&rsquo;s New
Atlantis: New Interdisciplinary Essays</em> (Texts in Culture),
Manchester/New York: Manchester University Press.</li>

<li>Rees, Graham, 1975, &ldquo;Francis Bacon&rsquo;s Semi-Paracelsian
Cosmology&rdquo;, <em>Ambix</em>, 22(2): 81&ndash;101.
doi:10.1179/amb.1975.22.2.81</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, &ldquo;Introduction&rdquo;, to
 <a href="#OFB12">OFB XII</a>:
 xvii&ndash;lxxxiii.</li>

<li>Rossi, Paoli, 1957 [1968], <em>Francesco Bacone: dalla magia alla
scienza</em>, Bari: Laterza. Translated as <em>Francis Bacon: From
Magic to Science</em>, Sacha Rabinovitch (trans.), Chicago: University
of Chicago Press, 1968.</li>

<li>Rusu, Doina-Cristina, 2020, &ldquo;Spiders, Ants, and Bees:
Francis Bacon and the Methodology of Natural Philosophy&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#JV2020">Jalobeanu and Vida 2020</a>:
 27&ndash;51. doi:10.5840/jems20209212</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2021, &ldquo;Francis Bacon and His Fate in
the History and Philosophy of Science, 2010&ndash;2020&rdquo;,
<em>Epistemology &amp; Philosophy of Science</em>, 58(3):
206&ndash;220. doi:10.5840/eps202158353</li>

<li>Rusu, Doina&#8208;Cristina and Dana Jalobeanu, 2020, &ldquo;Giovan
Battista della Porta and Francis Bacon on the Creative Power of
Experimentation&rdquo;, <em>Centaurus</em>, 62(3): 381&ndash;392.
doi:10.1111/1600-0498.12341</li>

<li>Serjeantson, Richard, 2013, &ldquo;The Philosophy of Francis Bacon
in Early Jacobean Oxford, with an Edition of an Unknown Manuscript of
the <em>Valerius Terminus</em>&rdquo;, <em>The Historical
Journal</em>, 56(4): 1087&ndash;1106.
doi:10.1017/S0018246X13000307</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2016, &ldquo;Francis Bacon and the Late
Renaissance Politics of Learning&rdquo;, in <em>For the Sake of
Learning: Essays in Honor of Anthony Grafton</em> (Scientific and
Learned Cultures and Their Institutions 18), 2 volumes, Ann Blair and
Anja-Silvia Goeing (eds), Leiden/Boston: Brill, I: 195&ndash;211 (ch.
12),</li>

<li>Sessions, William A. (ed.), 1990, <em>Francis Bacon&rsquo;s Legacy
of Texts: The Art of Discovery Grows with Discovery</em> (Georgia
State Literary Studies 5), New York: AMS Press.</li>

<li>Shapiro, Barbara J., 1980, &ldquo;Sir Francis Bacon and the
Mid-Seventeenth Century Movement for Law Reform&rdquo;, <em>The
American Journal of Legal History</em>, 24(4): 331.
doi:10.2307/844906</li>

<li>Simon, Elliott M., 1988, &ldquo;Bacon&rsquo;s <em>New
Atlantis</em>&#8239;: The Kingdom of God and Man&rdquo;,
<em>Christianity &amp; Literature</em>, 38(1): 43&ndash;61.
doi:10.1177/014833318803800107</li>

<li>Stephens, James, 1975, <em>Francis Bacon and the Style of
Science</em>, Chicago and London: The University of Chicago
Press.</li>

<li>Studer, Heidi D., 1998, &ldquo;Francis Bacon on the Political
Dangers of Scientific Progress&rdquo;, <em>Canadian Journal of
Political Science</em>, 31(2): 219&ndash;234.
doi:10.1017/S0008423900019776</li>

<li>Vickers, Brian, 1968a, <em>Francis Bacon and Renaissance
Prose</em>, Cambridge: [Cambridge] University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; (ed.), 1968b, <em>Essential Articles for the
Study of Francis Bacon</em>, Hamden CT: Archon Books.</li>

<li>Weinberger, Jerry, 1980, &ldquo;Introduction&rdquo;, to <em>The
Great Instauration and New Atlantis</em>, by Francis Bacon, Jerry
Weinberger (ed.), Arlington Heights, IL: Harlan Davidson,
vii&ndash;xxix.</li>

<li>Whitney, Charles, 1989, &ldquo;Francis Bacon&rsquo;s
<em>Instauratio</em>: Dominion of and over Humanity&rdquo;,
<em>Journal of the History of Ideas</em>, 50(3): 371&ndash;390.
doi:10.2307/2709567</li>

<li>Wormald, Brian Harvey Goodwin, 1993, <em>Francis Bacon: History,
Politics, Science, 1561-1626</em> (Cambridge Studies in the History
and Theory of Politics), Cambridge/New York: Cambridge University
Press.</li>

<li>Zagorin, Perez, 2001, &ldquo;Francis Bacon&rsquo;s Concept
of Objectivity and the Idols of the Mind&rdquo;, <em>The British
Journal for the History of Science</em>, 34(4): 379&ndash;393.
doi:10.1017/S0007087401004411</li>

</ul>

